x^2
x \geq 0
g(x) = x^2
g^{-1}(g(x)) = x \implies \sqrt{x^2} = x
x \leq 0
g(-x) = (-x)^2 = x^2
g
\geq 0
g^{-1}(g(-x)) = -x \implies \sqrt{(-x)^2} = -x \implies \sqrt{x^2} = -x
|x|
\sqrt{x^2} = |x|
 \sqrt{x^2} = \begin{cases} x & x \geq 0\\ -x & x \leq 0 \end{cases} 
